00:15:30.495 --> 00:15:33.164
<i> you realize
 how removed you truly are</i>

00:15:33.164 --> 00:15:36.135
<i> from the ritual of death."</i>

00:15:36.135 --> 00:15:37.536
That was the most
run-on sentence

00:15:37.536 --> 00:15:39.170
I've ever written in my life,
but I liked it.

00:15:39.170 --> 00:15:42.340
( laughter )

00:15:42.340 --> 00:15:44.276
That was in the evening
in the burning ghat.

00:15:44.276 --> 00:15:45.644
<i> This is in the morning,
 back here</i>

00:15:45.644 --> 00:15:47.645
<i> at 4:30 in the morning.</i>

00:15:47.645 --> 00:15:49.114
<i>Very challenging to get access.</i>

00:15:49.114 --> 00:15:50.315
<i> You are not supposed to
 photograph here.</i>

00:15:50.315 --> 00:15:52.551
<i> It took me three days
 to get access.</i>

00:15:52.551 --> 00:15:54.753
<i> Very powerful place to be,
 you see...</i>

00:15:54.753 --> 00:15:57.956
<i> the goats eating flowers,
 the dogs,</i>

00:15:57.989 --> 00:15:59.791
<i> that's a femur bone.</i>

00:15:59.791 --> 00:16:03.461
<i> These are all the ashes and
 bodies that have been burned.</i>

00:16:03.461 --> 00:16:06.631
And the belief is that if...

00:16:06.631 --> 00:16:08.533
you are burned
on the bank of the Ganges,

00:16:08.533 --> 00:16:12.437
and in Varanasi specifically,
and your ashes are thrown

00:16:12.437 --> 00:16:13.671
<i> into the Ganges river,</i>

00:16:13.671 --> 00:16:16.474
<i> which you are seeing
 right here that is human ash,</i>

00:16:16.474 --> 00:16:19.077
<i> that you will achieve
 a level of Moksha</i>

00:16:19.077 --> 00:16:20.212
<i> in the Hindu religion.</i>

00:16:20.212 --> 00:16:21.480
<i> And Moksha means,
 you will break</i>

00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:22.948
<i> the cycle of
 birth and rebirth.</i>

00:16:22.948 --> 00:16:24.883
<i> You'll not come back
 into this world,</i>

00:16:24.883 --> 00:16:27.052
<i> you'll not come back
 as a cricket or cow or</i>

00:16:27.052 --> 00:16:28.420
<i> another human, whatever.</i>

00:16:28.420 --> 00:16:30.188
<i> You will actually
 go to heaven.</i>

00:16:30.188 --> 00:16:33.592
So, many people actually
will come to die in Varanasi,

00:16:33.592 --> 00:16:36.829
it is that important to them
to reach heaven this way.

00:16:36.829 --> 00:16:40.331
And one challenge though,
of course is

00:16:40.331 --> 00:16:43.335
burning all these bodies uses
a tremendous amount of wood.

00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:47.539
It can take 1100 pounds of
logs to burn one large body.

00:16:47.539 --> 00:16:49.074
50-60 million trees

00:16:49.074 --> 00:16:51.076
from the Himalaya
are getting cut down.

00:16:51.076 --> 00:16:54.546
You see them getting barged up
to the burning ghat here,

00:16:54.546 --> 00:16:57.215
very complicated situation.

00:16:57.215 --> 00:16:59.984
<i> And of course this is
 a very common sight</i>

00:16:59.984 --> 00:17:01.486
<i> when you get further
 downstream.</i>

00:17:01.486 --> 00:17:03.287
<i> This is just 200 yards
 from the Ganges,</i>

00:17:03.287 --> 00:17:06.191
<i>this is a very typical drainage.</i>

00:17:06.191 --> 00:17:08.627
Of course,
it stems much in part from

00:17:08.627 --> 00:17:09.861
'the Ganges is God'.

00:17:09.861 --> 00:17:11.596
I mean, the Ganges is
going to clean itself.

00:17:11.596 --> 00:17:14.399
That isn't a big deal
if you pollute God.

00:17:14.399 --> 00:17:16.167
God is all-powerful.

00:17:16.167 --> 00:17:18.636
God is however we perceive it.

00:17:18.636 --> 00:17:21.873
<i> We moved further downstream
 all the way to Patna,</i>

00:17:21.873 --> 00:17:23.408
<i> a place few people go.</i>

00:17:23.408 --> 00:17:25.977
<i> And of course, we left the
 crazy monsoon storm</i>

00:17:25.977 --> 00:17:29.114
<i> with three feet at the top
 and we entered into a cyclone.</i>

00:17:29.114 --> 00:17:30.114
<i> We figured, what the hell,</i>

00:17:30.114 --> 00:17:31.983
<i> we've gotta make it
 to the end though.</i>

00:17:31.983 --> 00:17:34.653
<i> It was raining so hard,
 my eyelids were peeling back.</i>

00:17:34.653 --> 00:17:37.222
<i> I felt like I had a
 sand blaster on my face.</i>

00:17:37.222 --> 00:17:38.757
<i> It didn't stop these guys.</i>

00:17:38.757 --> 00:17:41.259
<i> These guys are out
 celebrating at full tilt</i>

00:17:41.259 --> 00:17:43.028
<i> a festival called Durga Puja,</i>

00:17:43.028 --> 00:17:45.263
<i> good over evil,
 and they build big,</i>

00:17:45.263 --> 00:17:46.497
<i> big statues of
 their deities and</i>

00:17:46.497 --> 00:17:47.699
<i> they bring them down
 and of course,</i>

00:17:47.699 --> 00:17:50.501
<i> they offer them to Ma Ganga,
 mother Ganges.</i>

00:17:50.501 --> 00:17:52.838
<i> Offer these offerings
 to the God.</i>

00:17:52.838 --> 00:17:54.739
Of course,
the river is bigger now.

00:17:54.739 --> 00:17:56.541
It has got a bigger current,
it is wider.

00:17:56.541 --> 00:17:58.744
But all of these offerings
just sort of float

00:17:58.744 --> 00:18:00.645
and collect on the banks.

00:18:00.645 --> 00:18:02.848
And many of them have
led paint and plastic,

00:18:02.848 --> 00:18:05.750
and what not. They are not
all biodegradable.

00:18:05.750 --> 00:18:08.587
<i> Further downstream,
 we moved across</i>

00:18:08.587 --> 00:18:11.323
<i> into Bengal, the last state
 on the Ganges.</i>

00:18:11.323 --> 00:18:14.059
<i> Durga Puja continued and raged
 through the night here.</i>

00:18:14.059 --> 00:18:15.927
<i> All the villagers were
 building their statues and</i>

00:18:15.927 --> 00:18:18.730
<i> coming and giving offering,
 putting ghee on the mouths and</i>

00:18:18.730 --> 00:18:20.031
<i> then carrying them,
 and then</i>

00:18:20.031 --> 00:18:22.734
<i> throwing them in the Ganges
 as a great offering.</i>

00:18:22.734 --> 00:18:24.836
<i> In Calcutta,
 on the southern edge,</i>

00:18:24.836 --> 00:18:27.806
<i>in the Indian side of the delta,</i>

00:18:27.806 --> 00:18:30.708
<i> we've now come
 about 1500 miles.</i>

00:18:30.708 --> 00:18:32.944
<i> This is one of the
 main shipping lanes</i>

00:18:32.944 --> 00:18:35.814
<i> for Calcutta and a very
 typical scene, you have</i>

00:18:35.814 --> 00:18:39.117
<i> somebody praying,
